description.narrative: Support the establishment of a sound private, well-functioning, equitable financial sector that fulfills critical roles in a market economy, most importantly financial intermediation – the efficient generation and allocation of savings to their most productive use.

This award strives to support the establishment of a sound private, well-functioning, equitable financial sector that fulfills critical roles in a market economy. More specifically, this includes Technical assistance will improve audit capacity on international issues, and assisting in implementation of standards and measures stemming from OECD’s Base Erosion and Profit Shifting (BEPS) initiative and automatic exchange of information (AEOI). The emphasis will be on case development, reviewing and providing recommendations on transfer pricing regulations, and reviewing implementation of BEPS action items related to transfer pricing.. Technical assistance will focus on improving audit capacity on international issues, and assisting in implementation of standards and measures stemming from OECD’s Base Erosion and Profit Shifting (BEPS) initiative and automatic exchange of information (AEOI). The emphasis will be on engagements narrowly focused on international issues, as opposed to larger projects of which international issues would be one part. The list of countries participating in the project is still being developed.. Project is in its initial stages. Collaboration trains new auditors and attorneys at the Zambia Revenue Authority (ZRA) in basic transfer pricing audit and interview techniques. ZRA will improve audit skills for all transfer pricing auditors by: 1) Strengthening audit techniques on transfer pricing issues within specific industries such as agriculture, telecoms, and financial institutions; assuring new TP auditors are capable of performing audit assignments; providing support to legal staff in areas where they can assist auditors in case development and settlement; using the Exchange of Information (EOI) treaty article in transfer pricing cases; and employing risk analysis tools for potential transfer pricing cases. Activities in 2019 will help the ZRA establish a transparent and defensible method for selection of returns for transfer pricing audits; allow for factual development of transfer pricing cases so that ZRA Audit and Legal departments can determine a settlement or litigation strategy; and help the ZRA establish a Competent Authority function and the capacity to respond accurately and timely to EOI requests and other treaty requirements.. Technical assistance will focus on improving audit capacity on international issues, and assisting in implementation of standards and measures stemming from OECD’s Base Erosion and Profit Shifting (BEPS) initiative and automatic exchange of information (AEOI). The emphasis will be on engagements narrowly focused on international issues, as opposed to larger projects of which international issues would be one part. Tanzania and Zambia will be the first countries involved in this project.. Project is in initial stages. Project has been completed.
